nse schemas now use `envelope(SuccessSchema)`; all 4xx/5xx use `ErrorEnvelopeSchema`. Removed imports of `errorMessage` (from `api-errors.ts`) and `ErrorResponseSchema` / `OkResponseSchema` / `UsernameCooldownResponseSchema` (from `validators.ts`) — legacy helpers still live there for the cleanup iteration.\n180\t  - Renamed `catch (err)` bindings to `catch (fetchError|updateError|queryError|insertError)` to avoid shadowing the imported `err` helper.\n181\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/profile.test.ts`:\n182\t    - Success assertions now destructure `.data` from envelopes (challenge/verify, `/profile/me`, `PUT /username`, `/public-profile/:userId` still unwrapped since that route converts in a later iteration).\n183\t    - 409 USERNAME_TAKEN: asserts `body.ok === false` + `body.error.code === \"USERNAME_TAKEN\"`.\n184\t    - 429 cooldown: asserts envelope shape, `body.error.code === \"USERNAME_COOLDOWN\"`, `retryable: true`, and `details.nextEditAvailableAt` present.\n185\t    - Invalid-format username tests: status 400 → 422 (both \"too short\" and \"missing body\"); `body.error.code === \"INVALID_USERNAME\"`; `details` is the Zod issue array.\n186\t    - `POST /confirm-tx` missing body: status 400 → 422; `body.error.code === \"VALIDATION_FAILED\"`.\n187\t    - Renamed the two \"returns 400 for ...\" tests to \"returns 422 for ...\" to match the new behavior.\n188\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/profile-me-zeroed.test.ts`: `toMatchObject` now wraps the expected shape in `{ ok: true, data: {...} }`.\n189\t- **Verification**:\n190\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n191\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n192\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/profile-me-zeroed.test.ts` → 1/1 passed\n193\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/profile.test.ts` → 13/13 passed\n194\t  - Full unit suite (`pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n195\t\n196\t## Iter