ead of `body1.nextCursor`.\n335\t- **Verification**:\n336\t  - `pnpm -C backend typecheck:self` → exit 0\n337\t  - `pnpm -C backend lint:self` → exit 0\n338\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/points-and-crates-routes.test.ts` → 6/6 passed\n339\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/openapi-contract.test.ts src/__tests__/waitlist-contract.test.ts` → 49/49 passed\n340\t  - Full unit suite (`vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n341\t\n342\t## Iteration 15 — 2026-04-22T10:35:17Z — OK\n343\t- **Log**: iteration-015.log\n344\t\n345\t## Iteration 16 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n346\t- **Item**: [routes] Convert `backend/src/routes/dogpile.ts` to envelope responses; update `dogpile-public-routes.test.ts` and the dogpile passthrough test in `public-referral-routes.test.ts`.\n347\t- **Changes**:\n348\t  - Rewrote both dogpile routes in `backend/src/routes/dogpile.ts`:\n349\t    - `GET /current`: success → `ok(c, <event-or-null>)`. All three branches (active, scheduled, empty) now emit the envelope. Empty case returns `200 { ok: true, data: null }` per FR-7 (documented success with null payload). 200 schema uses `envelope(DogpileCurrentResponseSchema)` — the inner schema is already `.nullable()`, so `data: <event | null>` falls out naturally without a wrapping object. `500 PRECONDITION_FAILED` for DB failures.\n350\t    - `GET /schedule`: success → `ok(c, { items })` with empty array being documented success. `500 PRECONDITION_FAILED` for DB failures.\n351\t  - Both 2xx schemas now use `envelope(SuccessSchema)`; all 5xx use `ErrorEnvelopeSchema`. Dropped the `errorMessage` import from `api-errors.ts` and the `ErrorResponseSchema` import from `validators.ts` (legacy helpers still live there for the cleanup iteration).\n352\t  - Renamed `catch (err)` bindings to `catch (queryError)` to avoid shadowing the imported `err` helper.\n353\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/do